def: To serve as a medium for conveying; to transmit, as heat,light, electricity, etc.
The knowledge of a sciolist; superficial knowledge.
In wool; with woolen raiment next the skin. [Obs.]
To render parallel to a certain line or direction; to bringinto the same line, as the axes of telescopes, etc.; to renderparallel, as rays of light.
A third person, who is to decide a controversy or questionsubmitted to arbitrators in case of their disagreement. Blackstone.
Having the blue color of the sky; azure; as, a sky-blue stone.Wordsworth.
The muscular system of an animal, or of any of its parts.

Any worm of the genus Lumbricus and allied genera, found indamp soil. One of the largest and most abundant species in Europe andAmerica is L. terrestris; many others are known; -- called alsoangleworm and dewworm.
